<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="100" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Distribution, habitat and phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="100">This new species is also endemic to Sa Pa, northern Vietnam and grows widely scattered on wet ground along road sides or along streams in evergreen broad-leaved forests, at an elevation of 1700-1890 m. Flowering from August to September and fruiting from September to October.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="100" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
The species epithet refers to the unusually long length of the corolla tube in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Oreocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oreocharis" order="Passeriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Oreocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="100" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
Endangered EN B2ab (iii), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="3. Youth Publishing, Ho Chi Minh City" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/technical-documents/categories-and-criteria" refId="B8" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN red list categories and criteria, Version 3.1 (2nd edn). IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland &amp; Cambridge. Available from: http://www.iucnredlist.org/technical-documents/categories-and-criteria" title="IUCN red list categories and criteria, Version 3.1 (2 nd edn). IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland &amp; Cambridge. Available from:" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/technical-documents/categories-and-criteria" year="2012">IUCN (2012)</bibRefCitation>
guidelines. This is based on an EOO of &lt;35 km2, being known from fewer than five populations and with disturbed locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
