has the longest tube amongst the yellow flowered species with infundibuliform corollas in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Oreocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oreocharis" order="Passeriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Oreocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is also the only species with coherent anthers amongst species in the previous, narrower concept 
<pageBreakToken pageId="7" pageNumber="102" start="start">of</pageBreakToken>
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Oreocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oreocharis" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Oreocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the current wider delimitation of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Oreocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oreocharis" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Oreocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the corolla tube is more similar in shape, though not in size, to those species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Ancylostemon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ancylostemon" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ancylostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Craib and 
